            <div class="latest-bikes-details-content">
                <p>@Html.Raw(@Model.BlogSummary.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p>
                <p>With an <span class="font-weight-700">expected starting price of ₹10,00,000,</span> the new Renault Duster aims to redefine what buyers can expect from a modern mid-size SUV. From turbocharged petrol engines and an upcoming strong hybrid powertrain to advanced driver-assistance systems, connected technology, and a bold new design language, the new Duster is clearly built for the future.</p>
                <p>This detailed article by<span class="font-weight-700"> BikeCarHub </span>explores everything the new Renault Duster has to offer — design, engines, features, technology, safety, driving experience, specifications, and much more — to help readers understand why this SUV could become a game-changer once again.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">A Fresh Design That Reflects Strength and Sophistication</h3>
                <p>The new Renault Duster takes a significant leap forward in design while staying true to its rugged DNA. It looks bolder, wider, and more premium than before, making it immediately recognisable on the road.</p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Distinctive Front-End Styling</h5>
                <p>At the front, the new Duster features a <span class="font-weight-700">new signature grille </span>that gives the SUV a strong visual identity. The grille integrates seamlessly with the <span class="font-weight-700">full LED headlamps </span>and sleek<span class="font-weight-700"> LED daytime running lights,</span> creating a sharp and modern appearance. The sculpted bonnet adds to the SUV’s muscular stance, reinforcing its off-road-ready personality.</p>
                <p>Renault has clearly focused on making the Duster look more global and sophisticated, ensuring it appeals to both urban buyers and adventure enthusiasts.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2026/april/renault duster/front.webp" alt="front" title="front" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>


                <h5 class="subheading">Rugged Yet Stylish Side Profile</h5>
                <p>From the side, the SUV stands tall thanks to its <span class="font-weight-700">high ground clearance of 212 mm,</span> which not only enhances its commanding road presence but also ensures confidence on rough roads. The <span class="font-weight-700">roof rails with a load-bearing capacity of 50 kg</span> highlight the Duster’s adventure-ready nature.</p>
                <p>The <span class="font-weight-700">45.72 cm (18-inch) “Adventure” black alloy wheels </span>add a sporty and premium touch, while subtle design lines along the body improve aerodynamics and visual appeal.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2026/april/renault duster/side.webp" alt="side" title="side" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <h5 class="subheading">Strong and Modern Rear Design</h5>
                <p>At the rear, the new Renault Duster features a <span class="font-weight-700">connected LED horizontal rear light bar,</span> giving it a wide and planted look. The bold tailgate design and robust bumper further emphasise the SUV’s strength. </p>
                <p>Overall, the exterior design successfully blends toughness with modern styling — a combination that has always been central to the Duster’s identity. </p>
                <div class="google-ad">
                    <ins class="adsbygoogle"
                         style="display:inline-block;width:1000px;height:200px"
