                <h3 class="subheading">Interior Design: Comfort Meets Smart Innovation</h3>
                <p>Step inside the new Renault Duster, and it becomes clear that this SUV is no longer just about ruggedness. The interior reflects Renault’s focus on comfort, technology, and a premium driving experience. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Digital and Driver-Focused Cabin</h5>
                <p>The highlight of the cabin is the <span class="font-weight-700">26.03 cm digital instrument cluster, </span>which supports<span class="font-weight-700"> map replication,</span> ensuring the driver gets navigation information right in their line of sight. This feature significantly enhances convenience, especially during long journeys. </p>
                <p>The elevated centre console with an <span class="font-weight-700">e-shifter </span>adds a modern touch while improving ergonomics. </p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2026/april/renault duster/wheel.webp" alt="wheel" title="wheel" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>
                <h5 class="subheading">Premium Comfort Features</h5>
                <p>Renault has equipped the new Duster with several comfort-oriented features to enhance every drive: </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Automatic dual-zone air conditioning </span>for personalised climate control</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Wireless smartphone charging </span>for added convenience</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Clean air AQI display with PM 2.5 filter, </span>ensuring healthier cabin air</li>
                    <li>High-quality upholstery and refined interior materials</li>
                </ul>
                <p>These features make the Duster equally suitable for daily city commutes and long highway trips.</p>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center image-height"><img src="~/images/blogs/2026/april/renault duster/display.webp" alt="display" title="display" loading="lazy" /></div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="subheading">OpenR Link Multimedia System with Google Built-In</h3>
                <p>One of the biggest upgrades in the new Renault Duster is the <span class="font-weight-700">OpenR Link multimedia system with Google built-in. </span>This advanced infotainment system brings a connected, intuitive, and user-friendly experience. </p>
                <h5 class="subheading">Key Highlights of OpenR Link</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Real-time navigation </span>powered by Google Maps</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Voice control </span>for hands-free operation</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Access to the Play Store, </span>allowing users to download compatible apps</li>
                    <li>Seamless smartphone integration</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This system transforms the cabin into a smart digital space, making every journey more enjoyable. BikeCarHub believes this feature alone places the new Duster ahead of many rivals in its segment. </p>

